---
import DemoLayout from '../../layouts/DemoLayout.astro';
import OcrReconstructionIsland from '../../islands/demos/OcrReconstruction.svelte';
---

<DemoLayout
  slug="ocr-reconstruction"
  title="OCR Reconstruction"
  summary="Messy OCR blocks are reordered into readable columns, captions, and paragraphs with editable layout."
  context="OCR systems usually return disconnected rectangles, not a coherent reading surface. This demo starts from that messy capture and reconstructs a document with reading order, role inference, and measured body columns. It is less about visual spectacle and more about showing Pretext as a reconstruction layer for real products."
  apis={['prepare()', 'layout()', 'layoutNextLine()']}
  difficulty="Advanced"
  snippet={`import { prepare, layout, layoutNextLine, buildFont } from '@chenglou/pretext';

const bodyText = sortBlocksByReadingOrder(ocrBlocks)
  .filter((block) => block.role === 'body')
  .map((block) => block.text)
  .join(' ');

const font = buildFont(15, 'Georgia, serif');
const prepared = prepare(bodyText, font);
const captionHeight = layout(prepare(caption, font), 210, 22).height;

let cursor = { segmentIndex: 0, graphemeIndex: 0 };
for (const column of reconstructedColumns) {
  while (column.hasRoom()) {
    const line = layoutNextLine(preparedBody, cursor, column.width);
    if (!line) break;
    drawLine(line.text, column.x, column.y);
    cursor = line.end;
  }
}`}
>
  <div class="demo-area" slot="demo">
    <OcrReconstructionIsland client:only="svelte" />
  </div>

  <div class="demo-info" slot="info">
    <div class="info-card">
      <h3>What this demonstrates</h3>
      <p>
        Reconstruction of a readable document from noisy OCR boxes. The raw blocks preserve rough
        geometry, but the rebuilt document infers headline, caption, note, and body roles before
        measuring the clean reading flow.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card">
      <h3>Relevant Pretext API</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><code>prepare()</code> + <code>layout()</code> for compact role-specific blocks</li>
        <li><code>layoutNextLine()</code> for the reconstructed body columns</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="info-card">
      <h3>Why this matters</h3>
      <p>
        This is the sort of product problem where DOM measurement is too late in the pipeline. A
        reconstruction layer needs to estimate the cleaned document before export, not after a full
        HTML rendering pass.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</DemoLayout>
